sentences: Peter William Nelson (born June 12, 1978), better known by his stage name Copywrite, is an underground hip hop artist from Columbus, Ohio.
In 2002, Copywrite released his debut album, The High Exhaulted, on Eastern Conference.
In 2002, Copywrite released his debut album, The High Exhaulted, on Eastern Conference.
In 2010, Copywrite released his second album, entitled The Life and Times of Peter Nelson.
In 2012, Copywrite released his third album, God Save the King, on Man Bites Dog Records.
In 2016, Copywrite released Blood, Bath & Beyond on Public School Records.
In 2019, Copywrite released Cruise control Vol.2,a mixtape released on www.bandcamp.com/Copywrite
Copywrite is the grandson of the late singer Skip Nelson (born as Scipione Mirabella) who most notably sang and played piano/guitar for the Glenn Miller Band in the 1940s.
